args:
Suddenly finding it rather difficult to get dates,
Orion seeks help from his Halidom companions.
Though hesitant, Cleo and Elisanne volunteer
to help him understand how women think.
Women have rather high ideals, Orion.\nI hope you know what you are\ngetting yourself into.
I would be happy to learn anything you\nhave to teach me, fair maiden.
I shall reach ANY ideal the ladies\nof the world wish of me.
You see? Just that answer reveals how\nvery far you have to go!
First things first: No one will be won\nover by a man who pursues any woman\nunlucky enough to enter his field of vision.

I know that if I were on the receiving end
of such behavior, I would be not charmed,
but wary. And I'm certain the vast majority
of women agree with me in this.
But I do not simply call out to any woman\nwho happens to wander by!
From what I've seen, you call out to\nliterally every woman you see.
Because I fall in LOVE\nwith every woman I see!
Every meeting I have is ordained by fate,\nwhich means they are all deadly serious!
You seem to think this is flippant,\nbut I assure you, it is not.
You may truly believe that, but I promise\nyou are the only one who does.
Impossible! I'll not stand here and\nlisten to this another minute!
This is no time to be sulking, Orion.\nInstead, hear what I have to say.
*sigh* Very well. My breast is bared.\nUnleash your cruelest arrows, milady.
If you act the instant an idea enters your\nhead, it will never resonate with people.
This is actually something you need to\napply to your life in general as opposed\nto simply your romantic endeavors.
You are a bodyguard—you have the ability\nto build relationships over time. Do that.
But must a man not strike\nwhile the iron is hot?!
If I pass on a first opportunity,\nthere is no promise of a second!
Patience is often a virtue when it comes\nto making lasting relationships.
Truly. And on that note,\nit's time to practice.
Then we are going into town? Ha ha!\nNOW I'm excited. Let us make haste!
No. You are going to pretend to be\nescorting one of us—WITHOUT any\nhint of flirting or romantic attachment.
Ah! Excellent! So which of you will it be?\nCleo? Or Elisanne?
It's too soon to let you loose on the town,\nOrion. It would only end in tragedy.
Oh, and we're going to be judging you\nSUPER strict, so take this seriously.
I shall behave as a model gentleman.
Just so we are clear, there will be NO\nthoughtless invitations or flirting during\nthis exercise.
Right, here we go. Ahem! Mi mi miii...\n＂Gee willikers, Orion! Thanks so much\nfor escorting me today!＂
(Think, man! Think of the perfect\nresponse for this situation!)
＂Well, this is my stop. Thanks again!＂
(What is the perfect thing one can say\nin this moment...? Yes, of course!)
＂It was nothing, my sweet maiden.\nI'm simply pleased you came to no harm.＂
Hmm. I suppose we have to count that\nas a passing grade, coming from yo—

＂And yet! It would be such a shame to let
this chance meeting go to waste.
Join me for tea, and I will satisfy
your every wanton—＂
You invited me for TEA, you idiot!\n...And wontons, maybe?
But I waited a moment before doing so!
An acceptable thing to say in this situation\nis ＂I would be happy to escort you again.＂
I quite agree. You should start as friends\nbefore attempting to become more.
I never would have thought of that.\nOh, I feel my confidence slipping away!
NOW do you understand what\nyou need to be focusing on?
At the very least, resist the urge\nto flirt with people the literal\nsecond after you meet them.
If you can master that,\nit'll go a long way.
Hmm... Resisting the urge to do\nsomething isn't really my way.
But ladies are going to see you\nmuch more favorably if you DO.
You want to turn your bad luck around,\nright? Then give this a shot!
I will take responsibility for my words\nand show you just how serious I am!
Do not let this lesson go to waste.
I won't. Next time, you will see a new me!
But first I need to find someone to show\nmy patience WITH—so I'm going to find\na woman in need of an escort! Ta taaa!
Well, he certainly went off in high spirits.
You can do it, Orion! We believe in you!\n...For the most part. ...I think?
